WEBVTT

00:01:48.422 --> 00:01:53.323
Birinchi Maharaj is great.

00:01:53.413 --> 00:01:57.967
Birinchi Maharaj is great!

00:02:26.788 --> 00:02:28.380
Where from?

00:02:29.748 --> 00:02:32.178
We are returning from Debraj.

00:02:33.838 --> 00:02:35.643
Kashi!
- Yes.

00:02:37.188 --> 00:02:39.115
Haven't been there in a long time.

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:43.018
Oh! Your work was in Kashi...

00:02:44.123 --> 00:02:47.223
Too crowded.

00:02:47.413 --> 00:02:49.887
That is true. But still...

00:02:50.173 --> 00:02:53.763
I had said at the very start
you have created a great city,

00:02:54.032 --> 00:02:57.898
but will it remain like it is?

00:02:58.567 --> 00:03:01.510
So many storms will blow over it,

00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.010
so many will come and go.

00:03:09.607 --> 00:03:12.860
One day, Sankar came to me
and said,

00:03:13.260 --> 00:03:15.865
even if you don't follow
the philosophy of One God,

00:03:16.100 --> 00:03:19.310
don't you agree that Gautam
caused a lot of destruction?

00:03:19.593 --> 00:03:22.000
Don't you think some action
should be taken for this?

00:03:23.382 --> 00:03:26.020
I said, if you want to,
then take action.

00:03:26.503 --> 00:03:30.603
If that's what will get you
peace of mind, then do it.

00:03:31.632 --> 00:03:36.302
But remember this that someone will
mess up your work as well some day.

00:03:36.658 --> 00:03:39.972
Someone will play football with
your religion. Understand that well.

00:03:42.630 --> 00:03:45.293
That lad had something in him

00:03:45.918 --> 00:03:49.178
but he could not master
the science of life.

00:03:49.795 --> 00:03:53.723
That's why, at the age of 32...

00:04:36.180 --> 00:04:40.950
Wake up!

00:04:41.040 --> 00:04:45.180
Wake up!

00:04:45.398 --> 00:04:49.523
Wake up!

00:04:54.052 --> 00:04:56.322
I don't have a moment of peace.

00:04:56.347 --> 00:04:59.350
I have to awaken this lad every
day from his sleep.

00:05:02.155 --> 00:05:04.140
Baba.
- What happened?

00:05:04.798 --> 00:05:07.503
My mind is at unrest, Baba.

00:05:09.670 --> 00:05:10.847
What is your name?

00:05:10.937 --> 00:05:13.642
My name is Guropodo Mitter.
Advocate.

00:05:15.038 --> 00:05:16.665
Come here, child.

00:05:19.887 --> 00:05:21.650
Touch his feet.

00:05:24.328 --> 00:05:25.363
Sit.

00:05:26.690 --> 00:05:31.675
This is my younger daughter, Baba.
Her name is Buchki. I mean, Neelima.

00:05:32.148 --> 00:05:35.532
Her mother died last year.

00:05:36.643 --> 00:05:39.688
Since then, Baba,
there has been no peace.

00:05:42.453 --> 00:05:44.822
I've visited Kashi
and Vrindavan but

00:05:45.335 --> 00:05:48.240
still I cannot find
the strength to go on.

00:05:50.075 --> 00:05:52.600
Cannot find the strength?
- No, Baba.

00:05:53.293 --> 00:05:56.482
It's as if there's no pillar left
for support.

00:06:02.157 --> 00:06:05.225
Hold this!

00:06:09.018 --> 00:06:10.740
Hold it tight.

00:06:11.983 --> 00:06:18.648
What? Is there any unrest left?
Is there any sadness left?

00:06:18.983 --> 00:06:21.362
Do you feel the spirit?
Any tiredness?

00:06:21.387 --> 00:06:24.185
Any emptiness left?
Any restrictions left?

00:06:31.913 --> 00:06:34.455
It's fate.

00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:43.003
Oh, God!

00:06:44.300 --> 00:06:46.917
Oh God.
- What happened?

00:06:47.525 --> 00:06:49.062
Nitai?

00:06:49.802 --> 00:06:52.515
If only I could find a good Babaji,

00:06:53.088 --> 00:06:55.655
I'd leave everything
and go with him.

00:06:56.680 --> 00:06:57.968
Why?

00:07:04.985 --> 00:07:06.735
You've lost interest in the world?

00:07:07.495 --> 00:07:09.873
Mind is at unrest, brother.

00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:16.082
Life has sped by. At home,
the wife keeps complaining.

00:07:16.712 --> 00:07:19.015
At the office, there's a new boss.

00:07:19.285 --> 00:07:22.710
He is also... It's all rubbish!
Nothing feels good.

00:07:24.645 --> 00:07:27.143
If you know of any such man,
let me know.

00:07:27.350 --> 00:07:29.032
There's no Babaji
in your fate, Nitai.

00:07:29.122 --> 00:07:31.710
Your constant chatter
has made me lose my knight.

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:34.132
You know, in spiritual matters,

00:07:34.222 --> 00:07:36.805
talking less
is a primary condition.

00:07:40.577 --> 00:07:43.310
This young man
is an insurance agent.

00:07:43.857 --> 00:07:46.783
And to top it,
he can do Hatha Yoga.

00:07:47.128 --> 00:07:49.993
So, why can't I find
myself a Babaji?

00:07:50.367 --> 00:07:54.220
My case is intellectual.
You will not understand that.

00:07:56.788 --> 00:08:00.303
It can only be understood
by Paramadha Chatterjee.

00:08:02.890 --> 00:08:05.453
Are you in the habit of
chewing green chillies?

00:08:20.768 --> 00:08:22.333
Nitai.

00:08:23.492 --> 00:08:24.815
Yes?

00:08:25.205 --> 00:08:28.725
A sage has come to Jagganath Ghat.
Understand?

00:08:29.018 --> 00:08:30.730
He's called Mirchai Baba.

00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:38.545
People visiting him are being
offered enchanted green chillies

00:08:38.635 --> 00:08:41.172
and after eating them,
all their illness is cured.

00:08:44.543 --> 00:08:46.220
Will a Radio Baba work?

00:08:46.310 --> 00:08:48.885
Swami Taritananda!

00:08:49.222 --> 00:08:53.018
This Baba has two 'tives'.
One negative, one positive.

00:08:53.108 --> 00:08:58.405
Drains electricity from the sky
and sparks it to people. - Really?

00:08:58.622 --> 00:09:01.865
You go to him and you
will be cured of all disease.

00:09:03.283 --> 00:09:05.228
Electrotherapy!

00:09:08.992 --> 00:09:13.672
My disease is just one.
Lack of money.

00:09:16.138 --> 00:09:18.385
Let him find a nice
source of income for me

00:09:18.410 --> 00:09:20.912
and I'll accept that he's great!

00:09:20.978 --> 00:09:23.033
That too, he can do.
- He can?

00:09:24.850 --> 00:09:30.030
He will take you to a place for a
day, before the battle in 1914.

00:09:31.053 --> 00:09:32.652
Then?

00:09:33.335 --> 00:09:36.248
You will buy some iron.
- Iron?

00:09:37.653 --> 00:09:40.288
Yes. For cheap.
- Then?

00:09:42.918 --> 00:09:44.743
For cheap.
- Then?

00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:51.308
After that, you...
- After that, what?

00:09:54.183 --> 00:09:58.607
After 1914 what happened?

00:09:58.848 --> 00:10:01.332
Mate in two moves, brother.

00:10:01.483 --> 00:10:03.360
What happened after 1914?

00:10:03.572 --> 00:10:06.135
After 1914, he brings you
back to '65.

00:10:06.225 --> 00:10:08.162
With the iron?
- Yes, of course.

00:10:08.323 --> 00:10:10.453
And then you sell the iron
at the current rate.

00:10:11.167 --> 00:10:14.050
Current rate?

00:10:14.710 --> 00:10:16.803
Nibaran.

00:10:18.238 --> 00:10:20.190
What?
- Disaster!

00:10:20.280 --> 00:10:23.062
Sit.
- 400 rupees, 500 rupees.

00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:25.588
600 rupees. 700 rupees.

00:10:26.148 --> 00:10:28.927
Speak thee not!
- I have done it, brother.

00:10:29.017 --> 00:10:31.617
Narendrapur - five acres of land.
Three houses.

00:10:31.707 --> 00:10:33.698
Now all I need to do
is find the Babaji.

00:10:33.788 --> 00:10:36.713
Again Babaji?
- Chess is an intellectual game.

00:10:36.803 --> 00:10:38.945
This kind of pandemonium
does not go with it.

00:10:39.763 --> 00:10:42.868
He's destroyed everything.

00:10:43.023 --> 00:10:45.327
Buchki is getting an induction.
- What?

00:10:45.575 --> 00:10:47.568
Buchki is getting an induction.

00:10:47.658 --> 00:10:49.445
Some Babaji has inducted her father

00:10:49.535 --> 00:10:51.618
and now the daughter
will also get it.

00:10:52.395 --> 00:10:55.048
Did you go to their place? - Yes,
that's where I'm coming from.

00:10:55.318 --> 00:10:57.420
So is this good news or bad news?

00:10:57.510 --> 00:10:59.008
Getting inducted into priesthood
is good news?

00:10:59.098 --> 00:11:01.650
Why not? I too would get inducted
if I found a good sage.

00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:04.547
But I was to propose to her!

00:11:04.637 --> 00:11:06.518
So you propose...
- No, Nitai.

00:11:06.668 --> 00:11:09.663
You do not know
the background to this story,

00:11:10.028 --> 00:11:14.385
and so you don't understand
the reason for Satta's anxiety.

00:11:14.580 --> 00:11:17.915
You need a little introduction.

00:11:20.170 --> 00:11:27.257
This Buchki is Alipore lawyer,
Guropodo Mitter's younger daughter.

00:11:27.438 --> 00:11:31.980
Mr Mitter's wife, Soudamini,
was Takdar Shashi Ghosh's daughter.

00:11:32.070 --> 00:11:33.780
Is that so?
- Yes.

00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:37.455
She died a year or two ago.

00:11:38.258 --> 00:11:42.598
I know them through my childhood
friend from Bagbazar,

00:11:42.623 --> 00:11:45.733
the famous Professor Nani.

00:11:46.250 --> 00:11:50.627
Nani's wife is Mr Mitter's
eldest daughter, Nirupama.

00:11:50.717 --> 00:11:53.593
Fine.
- It was in Nirupama's house

00:11:53.852 --> 00:11:57.700
that Master Satta
first met Lady Buchki.

00:11:57.987 --> 00:12:01.255
It was love at first sight
and since then,

00:12:01.345 --> 00:12:03.640
he's contemplating marriage.

00:12:06.133 --> 00:12:07.880
Clear?
- Clear.

00:12:08.138 --> 00:12:13.595
So the point is, Master Satta
has fallen in love with Lady Buchki

00:12:14.033 --> 00:12:17.790
but Lady Buchki wants to get
inducted into priesthood.

00:12:17.947 --> 00:12:21.672
Hence, the matter is very serious.
- Exactly.

00:12:22.463 --> 00:12:24.280
Satta, carry on.

00:12:24.972 --> 00:12:27.238
Fatik, get some tea.

00:12:27.457 --> 00:12:30.810
They returned from Kashi yesterday.

00:12:31.075 --> 00:12:34.713
I would have visited them
yesterday but at the laundry,

00:12:34.803 --> 00:12:40.007
my bloody pants were not ready
so I had to wait for one day.

00:12:40.525 --> 00:12:45.282
So then, today, at around eight in
the morning, I went to their place.

00:12:46.098 --> 00:12:49.225
On reaching it, I noticed
that the place seemed strange.

00:12:49.710 --> 00:12:52.297
The guards were all huddled
together and talking.

00:12:52.533 --> 00:12:54.278
The usual Radio Ceylon was not
playing.

00:12:54.303 --> 00:12:55.788
Everything seemed different.

00:12:56.435 --> 00:12:59.548
Anyway, I entered the house
and was going up the stairs

00:12:59.638 --> 00:13:01.377
when someone called me from behind.

00:13:01.640 --> 00:13:03.702
I turned and who do I see?
Ganesh Mama! - Satta.

00:13:03.923 --> 00:13:06.240
Wait a minute! Who is Ganesh Mama?

00:13:06.517 --> 00:13:09.638
Ganesh Mama
is Mr Mitter's brother-in-law.

00:13:09.818 --> 00:13:13.382
Lady Buchki's uncle. Clear?
- Clear.

00:13:13.935 --> 00:13:15.358
And then?

00:13:16.465 --> 00:13:18.408
Buchki is not there?

00:13:18.498 --> 00:13:21.425
She is. But there is work
going on upstairs.

00:13:21.515 --> 00:13:23.722
Buchki's father is getting inducted
into priesthood.

00:13:23.812 --> 00:13:27.362
Priesthood? - Why should the word
priesthood make you smile like that?

00:13:27.588 --> 00:13:29.675
Do you know his guru
is a great and learned man?

00:13:29.873 --> 00:13:33.110
He's been around since the time
the town of Kashi was constructed.

00:13:33.263 --> 00:13:36.300
Which Kashi?
- Kashi Benaras. Nut Kashi Khu Khu.

00:13:36.585 --> 00:13:38.552
Oh, God! Is he into black magic
of some sort?

00:13:38.642 --> 00:13:40.993
No, he's not into black magic
but he's a Democrat, for sure.

00:13:41.083 --> 00:13:43.735
You are a hardcore communist.
Now move along.

00:13:43.825 --> 00:13:46.953
Communist? - Yes. I've heard you go
out on protest marches on the roads.

00:13:47.043 --> 00:13:48.867
Oh that...
- No.

00:13:48.957 --> 00:13:51.870
You better leave today.
Come some other day to meet them.

00:13:51.960 --> 00:13:54.732
But...
- Leave.

00:13:58.183 --> 00:14:00.700
Your son-in-law is well, I hope.

00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:05.503
Has he got a job?
He was looking for one, wasn't he?

00:14:07.695 --> 00:14:09.943
Listen!

00:14:10.648 --> 00:14:11.755
You called me from behind?

00:14:11.845 --> 00:14:13.748
Do you know of any job or what?

00:14:13.838 --> 00:14:17.935
I do know of something but he
must be trying elsewhere.

00:14:18.025 --> 00:14:20.767
No. Nowadays nothing can happen
without a little backing.

00:14:20.857 --> 00:14:24.002
But Uncle, in case of backing,
what of his self-respect...

00:14:24.092 --> 00:14:27.788
You cannot understand, Sattaranjan.
Today's day and age is different.

00:14:27.878 --> 00:14:30.885
Go up and meet everyone quickly.
Then come and give me the details.

00:14:30.975 --> 00:14:33.697
Yes, then, I'll quickly...
- Yes, quickly.

00:14:34.553 --> 00:14:36.930
You wait.
I'll take just five minutes or so.

00:14:48.435 --> 00:14:49.463
Hey.

00:14:52.565 --> 00:14:53.548
Hey.

00:15:26.732 --> 00:15:28.658
Hey. Buchki.

00:15:29.118 --> 00:15:32.148
Are you calling me?
- What's the matter?

00:15:33.107 --> 00:15:36.480
What is this induction all about?
Your house has completely changed.

00:15:37.108 --> 00:15:40.247
I'm also getting inducted.
- Buchki.

00:15:41.048 --> 00:15:43.013
Didn't you get my letter?

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:46.090
Your letter?
- I wrote to you in Benaras.

00:15:46.493 --> 00:15:48.537
Was that you?

00:15:48.768 --> 00:15:51.320
A seven line letter! Of that,
two lines were from Shelley.

00:15:51.410 --> 00:15:54.033
Two lines from Chandidas
and two lines of a poem.

00:15:54.355 --> 00:15:56.658
Other than that, all it said was,
How are you? I'm fine!

00:15:56.748 --> 00:16:00.520
But believe me,
the feeling behind it all is mine.

00:16:00.743 --> 00:16:02.957
Keep your feelings to yourself.
- Listen.

00:16:03.047 --> 00:16:04.963
I have work.
- I need to talk.

00:16:05.120 --> 00:16:07.300
We'll see after I'm inducted.

00:16:13.013 --> 00:16:14.927
Then?
- Then what?

00:16:15.017 --> 00:16:16.455
I left the place.

00:16:18.515 --> 00:16:21.185
Nibaran, you have to help me.

00:16:23.775 --> 00:16:26.160
You deliver quotations
instead of love letters

00:16:26.470 --> 00:16:28.113
and I must rescue you.

00:16:28.203 --> 00:16:31.330
No, I can handle that part of it.
You just remove this Babaji.

00:16:31.532 --> 00:16:33.378
What if this person is genuine?

00:16:36.798 --> 00:16:39.485
So, you think he is genuine, Parak?

00:16:39.672 --> 00:16:42.540
I have an open mind.

00:16:42.927 --> 00:16:45.645
If he appeals to your intelligence,
that's great. Otherwise, reject him.

00:16:45.735 --> 00:16:47.943
Could we meet
and interview this Babaji?

00:16:48.033 --> 00:16:50.633
Does he sit at any place?
- I don't know.

00:16:51.838 --> 00:16:55.678
Did you see Buchki's sister?
Was she there?

00:16:56.155 --> 00:16:57.498
Yes. She was.

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:00.798
Then... One...

00:17:08.765 --> 00:17:11.178
How old is this Babaji? 2,000?

00:17:12.702 --> 00:17:15.200
Oh God! Paramadha.

00:17:15.728 --> 00:17:19.802
Sell him an insurance policy.
You will get many premiums.

00:17:21.488 --> 00:17:24.613
Hello? Is that Putli?

00:17:25.140 --> 00:17:28.150
Is your father there? No?

00:17:28.738 --> 00:17:34.005
Mother there? Put your mother on.
Say Uncle Nibaran is calling.

00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:38.217
He was talking about the days
when Kashi was born, right?

00:17:38.595 --> 00:17:40.485
Maybe he was talking about rebirth.

00:17:40.510 --> 00:17:42.590
After all, he is a
type of an astrologer.

00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:48.697
Is that sister-in-law? Fine.
Where is your husband?

00:17:50.978 --> 00:17:53.113
Experimenting again?

00:17:54.375 --> 00:17:59.090
Boiling grass? Why? Can't Nani
digest raw grass anymore?

00:18:02.968 --> 00:18:05.553
Here, protein synthesis
is taking place.

00:18:05.715 --> 00:18:08.915
The grass will get hydrolysed
and turn into carbohydrate.

00:18:09.540 --> 00:18:12.290
Then, if you leave
two amino groups,

00:18:12.380 --> 00:18:14.738
you get hexahydroxidiamino.

00:18:14.828 --> 00:18:16.553
What is this rubber pipe?

00:18:16.643 --> 00:18:18.923
Potli, play that once, my girl.

00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:40.458
Only bubbles?
- It's getting oxidized!

00:18:40.548 --> 00:18:42.742
Do come. The tea is getting cold.

00:18:42.832 --> 00:18:45.492
I thought music will flow
down the rubber pipe,

00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:49.285
mix with the grass and
create a fantastic green nectar.

00:18:54.725 --> 00:18:56.945
If I get successful with this,

00:18:57.035 --> 00:18:59.807
I think lack of fo...

00:19:00.428 --> 00:19:01.680
Lack of food?
- Yes.

00:19:01.917 --> 00:19:03.473
There will be no lack?
- That's right.

00:19:06.655 --> 00:19:07.918
Sister-in-law.

00:19:09.275 --> 00:19:11.833
Start practising how to chew.
Understood?

00:19:12.643 --> 00:19:17.095
Sure. What everybody does, I shall
too. What's the matter in that? Sit.

00:19:17.272 --> 00:19:19.943
Well, I haven't asked you
one thing, Nani.

00:19:20.033 --> 00:19:23.535
Will future humans walk
on two legs or four?

00:19:23.715 --> 00:19:26.433
The advantage of four legs is

00:19:26.833 --> 00:19:28.328
speed?
- Speed.

00:19:28.690 --> 00:19:31.595
Two plus two.

00:19:39.095 --> 00:19:41.613
Sister-in-law,
tell me about this Baba!

00:19:41.703 --> 00:19:43.640
Who are you talking about?
Birinchibaba?

00:19:43.730 --> 00:19:45.113
Is that his name?

00:19:46.758 --> 00:19:49.492
Potli! Keep a lookout on the grass.

00:19:49.582 --> 00:19:52.855
I am doing so, mother.
- Come.

00:19:53.898 --> 00:19:56.935
Tell me.
- What can all this be?

00:19:57.858 --> 00:20:00.565
I went home and saw that
my father was getting inducted.

00:20:01.828 --> 00:20:05.487
Since my mother died,
my father has changed.

00:20:07.228 --> 00:20:10.930
Stopped working.
Doesn't meet anyone.

00:20:11.490 --> 00:20:14.755
I thought that father's mind has...

00:20:15.502 --> 00:20:18.525
Anyway, now he has got Guruji.

00:20:18.815 --> 00:20:20.848
Guruji is everything.
- I guess so.

00:20:21.043 --> 00:20:24.150
So you are saying that this person
has kind of settled here.

00:20:25.985 --> 00:20:28.642
Something like a
semi-permanent settlement.

00:20:28.905 --> 00:20:32.033
Earlier, father was not
at all interested in religion.

00:20:32.503 --> 00:20:35.893
Something like what would happen
if you fall in love at an old age.

00:20:36.195 --> 00:20:39.310
Well, what is your view?
What do you make of it?

00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:42.928
He speaks pretty well.
Sounds good to hear.

00:20:43.078 --> 00:20:47.015
Though I don't follow all he says.
Some relevity, felevity.

00:20:47.105 --> 00:20:49.452
Relativity.

00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:51.543
Yes, that.

00:20:51.735 --> 00:20:54.648
Nani, you went too?
- Why him?

00:20:54.738 --> 00:20:58.333
Lawyer, barrister
and people from every corner.

00:20:58.423 --> 00:21:00.425
So many people have been
coming to hear him.

00:21:03.080 --> 00:21:05.960
Leonardo da Vinci.

00:21:07.525 --> 00:21:10.130
The man knows it all.
- Really?

00:21:10.865 --> 00:21:13.113
He's solved a lot of problems
in Czechoslovakia.

00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:15.000
Who? This Babaji?

00:21:16.040 --> 00:21:17.568
Einstein used to visit him.

00:21:17.823 --> 00:21:19.125
Visit him?
- Yes.

00:21:19.373 --> 00:21:21.210
He only taught him.
- What?

00:21:21.593 --> 00:21:25.760
Relativity. E=mc2

00:21:26.015 --> 00:21:27.770
Baba taught him?

00:21:29.193 --> 00:21:30.870
Taught Einstein?

00:21:31.943 --> 00:21:34.407
Is that what he said
in front of so many people?

00:21:34.607 --> 00:21:35.730
Yes.

00:21:36.795 --> 00:21:38.793
And people believed him?

00:21:41.123 --> 00:21:43.868
Everybody clapped.

00:21:45.403 --> 00:21:46.788
Goodness.

00:21:47.243 --> 00:21:49.498
Even you would have done the same.

00:21:49.932 --> 00:21:52.820
You tell me, how long
does a person live?

00:21:52.910 --> 00:21:55.340
Why not ask the person
who knows all this?

00:21:55.430 --> 00:21:58.338
Nani. - You tell me.
How long can a person live?

00:21:58.925 --> 00:22:01.505
Quite long, actually.
- How long?

00:22:01.595 --> 00:22:05.628
150? 200? - If it's 200,
then it's a tortoise.

00:22:07.315 --> 00:22:08.740
Not man?

00:22:09.200 --> 00:22:11.255
Not a homo sapien.

00:22:11.523 --> 00:22:14.368
And 2,000?
- 1,000?

00:22:14.542 --> 00:22:17.047
2,000. Could any man

00:22:17.137 --> 00:22:20.353
be alive since the construction
of Kashi?

00:22:21.135 --> 00:22:23.722
The tea is getting cold.
Why don't you drink it?

00:22:24.530 --> 00:22:26.323
What happened? Can he?

00:22:26.745 --> 00:22:29.408
His right-hand person
seems like a loafer.

00:22:29.715 --> 00:22:32.368
What, Nani?
- Trees can.

00:22:32.458 --> 00:22:34.465
Not homo sapiens.

00:22:36.070 --> 00:22:39.308
Tree. Bo Tree?

00:22:39.578 --> 00:22:43.058
Buddha's tree of enlightenment.
Remember?

00:22:45.152 --> 00:22:49.213
You are a scientist. He said
all this nonsense about Einstein

00:22:49.303 --> 00:22:51.150
in front of you
and you didn't expose him?

00:22:52.378 --> 00:22:54.072
And you're laughing?

00:22:55.035 --> 00:22:57.930
What's the use, my friend?
In the end, he'll accuse me

00:22:58.020 --> 00:23:01.917
of causing trouble
because I'm after his property.

00:23:04.090 --> 00:23:05.513
But it's interesting.
- What?

00:23:05.603 --> 00:23:09.000
He showed us something.
Come forward. I'll tell you.

00:23:09.615 --> 00:23:12.720
This is the present.

00:23:12.810 --> 00:23:14.178
Where?
- Here.

00:23:14.558 --> 00:23:16.108
At this contact point.
- Okay.

00:23:16.198 --> 00:23:18.445
And this right hand

00:23:19.735 --> 00:23:23.803
is rotating clockwise.

00:23:25.313 --> 00:23:26.848
Future.
- All right.

00:23:26.938 --> 00:23:29.472
And this.
- Anticlockwise.

00:23:29.623 --> 00:23:33.568
Anticlockwise. The past.
- Okay.

00:23:33.658 --> 00:23:35.430
He made both of them
move at the same time.

00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:37.180
At the same time?
- At the same time.

00:23:37.270 --> 00:23:39.450
In opposite directions?
- In opposite directions.

00:23:40.912 --> 00:23:42.768
So he says that
there is nothing like

00:23:42.793 --> 00:23:44.647
the present because
time does not stop.

00:23:52.757 --> 00:23:54.040
Difficult.

00:23:56.440 --> 00:23:59.090
Sister-in-law, can you do it?
Try it.

00:23:59.328 --> 00:24:00.745
Let me try.

00:24:01.283 --> 00:24:02.793
Yes, try!

00:24:04.055 --> 00:24:07.600
If he can't do it,
how will I be able to do it? No.

00:24:18.178 --> 00:24:20.070
Listen.
- To what?

00:24:20.360 --> 00:24:23.378
The voice of the Babaji.

00:24:41.727 --> 00:24:45.857
Time is a very strange thing.

00:24:46.515 --> 00:24:50.570
Time is a very strange thing.

00:24:50.985 --> 00:24:55.433
It is said people are here today
but not there tomorrow.

00:24:55.692 --> 00:24:59.502
I say, you're there tomorrow
but not here today.

00:25:00.237 --> 00:25:03.437
Tomorrow. This means time.

00:25:04.043 --> 00:25:06.698
Tomorrow is there.

00:25:07.027 --> 00:25:10.758
But today, the present

00:25:10.998 --> 00:25:16.465
does not exist. How can it exist?

00:25:16.915 --> 00:25:19.538
How can it exist?

00:25:20.060 --> 00:25:25.765
Time is constantly moving.

00:25:25.855 --> 00:25:30.113
It does not stay at one place.

00:25:30.292 --> 00:25:33.142
So how could you label
it as the present,

00:25:33.232 --> 00:25:35.918
tie chains around
its leg and hold it

00:25:36.008 --> 00:25:40.685
and say this is the present?

00:25:42.383 --> 00:25:44.988
The moment the words end,

00:25:45.455 --> 00:25:48.730
it becomes happened.

00:25:49.113 --> 00:25:53.560
Or has happened. Or had happened.

00:25:53.930 --> 00:25:57.130
All this means the past.

00:25:57.640 --> 00:26:00.167
Something that has gone.

00:26:00.373 --> 00:26:03.470
The past!
- The past!

00:26:03.630 --> 00:26:06.248
The past!
- The past!

00:26:06.338 --> 00:26:09.102
The past!
- The past!

00:26:10.732 --> 00:26:15.370
On this, I had verbal
arguments with Plato.

00:26:15.460 --> 00:26:17.450
Who is he talking about?

00:26:17.693 --> 00:26:19.857
Plato, the great Roman astrologer.

00:26:19.947 --> 00:26:22.283
Astrologer!
- Plato said,

00:26:22.605 --> 00:26:25.477
Inhuman logas cognosis.

00:26:25.953 --> 00:26:29.153
I cannot understand
what you are saying.

00:26:29.303 --> 00:26:31.695
I cannot understand
what you are saying.

00:26:33.062 --> 00:26:35.840
Dictos jargon paranois.

00:26:36.450 --> 00:26:38.813
You are talking gibberish.

00:26:43.508 --> 00:26:46.465
I said, well, fine then,

00:26:47.048 --> 00:26:49.135
if you cannot understand...

00:26:49.290 --> 00:26:52.665
If you cannot understand
what I'm saying,

00:26:52.848 --> 00:26:55.350
then I'll do a demonstration
for you.

00:26:55.710 --> 00:26:58.753
Plato said, oh my God,
what demonstration!

00:26:59.232 --> 00:27:01.715
He was quite scared of me.

00:27:02.430 --> 00:27:05.327
I said, why are you getting
scared, Plato?

00:27:05.417 --> 00:27:08.113
It's very simple. Look at this.

00:27:08.843 --> 00:27:13.115
This is my right hand.
This, my finger.

00:27:13.530 --> 00:27:17.915
Now, this starts rotating
on the right side, clockwise.

00:27:18.218 --> 00:27:22.673
Meaning, in the direction
where time goes.

00:27:22.898 --> 00:27:26.652
And where does time go?
Towards the future.

00:27:28.208 --> 00:27:33.585
And, this is my left hand.
This rotates on the left side.

00:27:34.222 --> 00:27:39.763
Anticlockwise. Signifying the past.

00:27:39.853 --> 00:27:44.570
The past.
- And now, they rotate together.

00:27:59.100 --> 00:28:02.670
Front and back.

00:28:03.558 --> 00:28:05.962
This is life.

00:28:07.165 --> 00:28:10.485
What was there. What will happen.

00:28:11.578 --> 00:28:14.285
That's what it is.

00:28:15.728 --> 00:28:19.188
Past and future.

00:28:19.818 --> 00:28:22.453
The world lies between these two.

00:28:23.733 --> 00:28:25.090
Outside!

00:28:26.432 --> 00:28:28.147
Outside.

00:28:29.815 --> 00:28:31.420
Come!

00:28:31.510 --> 00:28:34.853
Sit at the back there, understood?

00:28:35.248 --> 00:28:37.643
Don't worry so much.
We'll go and sit.

00:28:38.045 --> 00:28:39.615
After all,
we must disinfect our minds,

00:28:39.705 --> 00:28:42.882
which are so filled with sins.

00:28:45.813 --> 00:28:47.793
Come!

00:29:00.915 --> 00:29:02.860
Quickly, go and finish
the blessing part.

00:29:03.045 --> 00:29:04.447
Me?

00:29:04.537 --> 00:29:06.168
Yes, not another word. Go ahead.

00:29:21.990 --> 00:29:23.547
My Lord!

00:29:25.125 --> 00:29:26.383
Who is it?

00:29:27.843 --> 00:29:29.330
It's me.

00:29:30.278 --> 00:29:32.098
You look familiar.

00:29:32.790 --> 00:29:35.570
Where have I seen you before?
- Me?

00:29:35.758 --> 00:29:39.183
In Nepal? Have I seen you in Nepal?
- I stay on Serpentine Lane.

00:29:39.273 --> 00:29:42.012
What's your name!

00:29:42.102 --> 00:29:44.662
Sattaranjan Sarkar.

00:29:44.828 --> 00:29:47.665
Sattaranjan!

00:29:47.845 --> 00:29:50.335
Sattaranjan!

00:29:55.052 --> 00:29:56.903
Yes! Murshidabad.

00:29:57.588 --> 00:29:58.838
I remember now.

00:29:59.553 --> 00:30:02.065
In Jagath Seth's house.

00:30:02.867 --> 00:30:07.340
It was his mother's death ceremony
that day. There were many people.

00:30:07.855 --> 00:30:11.272
Raja Krishnachandra,
Rai Rayan Jankiprasad,

00:30:11.362 --> 00:30:15.127
Nawab Iftikhar Salar Khan
Khanan Mohabbat Jung.

00:30:16.233 --> 00:30:21.042
Amir Chand of Sutanati, the one
mentioned in History as UmiChand.

00:30:21.925 --> 00:30:27.648
Sethji treated us to a lot of food.

00:30:28.413 --> 00:30:33.050
But the sweets ran out while

00:30:33.365 --> 00:30:35.735
serving the Lords of Sutanati.

00:30:35.825 --> 00:30:39.868
So, they abused the host and left.

00:30:42.740 --> 00:30:44.195
Incredible!

00:30:44.572 --> 00:30:46.700
This is the perfect time to go
to him. He's in the right mood.

00:30:46.725 --> 00:30:48.418
Shall I go?
- Anyway.

00:30:49.633 --> 00:30:52.583
So, Motiram.
- Motiram?

00:30:53.058 --> 00:30:56.630
I knew you by that
name only, child.

00:30:57.080 --> 00:31:00.833
You were Sethji's accountant.

00:31:01.028 --> 00:31:05.360
So Motiram, you'd better chant

00:31:06.642 --> 00:31:09.948
the 'Dhurjati' mantra.

00:31:10.198 --> 00:31:13.773
Every morning, wake up
and chant it 108 times.

00:31:17.048 --> 00:31:19.725
Very fast, all right? Now go.

00:31:22.055 --> 00:31:27.028
Lord. What is better? The path
of urge or that of satisfaction?

00:31:27.243 --> 00:31:30.708
Fine question.

00:31:31.533 --> 00:31:35.702
Tulsi once asked me
the same question.

00:31:36.123 --> 00:31:41.382
Tulsidas! We eat food,

00:31:42.445 --> 00:31:44.538
don't we?
- Yes.

00:31:44.723 --> 00:31:46.970
But why do we eat?
- Why do we eat?

00:31:47.227 --> 00:31:49.295
Because we feel hungry.

00:31:49.385 --> 00:31:53.780
Because we feel hungry,
what do we eat?

00:31:54.863 --> 00:31:57.458
Rice, fruit, fish, meat, etc.

00:31:57.548 --> 00:32:00.253
Fish, meat.
- What happens

00:32:00.413 --> 00:32:02.245
when we eat?
- What happens?

00:32:02.335 --> 00:32:05.612
Our hunger is satisfied.
- It's satisfied.

00:32:05.793 --> 00:32:07.620
And so the root cause
- The root cause

00:32:07.710 --> 00:32:11.367
of consumption is urge
- Urge.

00:32:11.457 --> 00:32:15.025
and the result of consumption
is satisfaction. - Satisfaction.

00:32:15.115 --> 00:32:17.572
Isn't that so?
- Yes.

00:32:18.890 --> 00:32:20.177
Yes.

00:32:20.730 --> 00:32:22.773
Tulsi was a sage.

00:32:24.045 --> 00:32:25.762
I told him

00:32:26.105 --> 00:32:28.950
without consumption
there is no satisfaction.

00:32:29.660 --> 00:32:31.645
I said, Tulsi,

00:32:31.735 --> 00:32:35.623
if there is no consumption
how can there be satisfaction?

00:32:37.955 --> 00:32:40.982
So after Ramayan,
I changed him to King Mansingha.

00:32:41.225 --> 00:32:43.690
Told him to consume
as much as he wanted to.

00:32:44.485 --> 00:32:47.210
He earned a lot of wealth

00:32:47.487 --> 00:32:49.458
but nothing remained with him.

00:32:49.667 --> 00:32:53.438
He married the daughter of a Bengali
Jagatsingha and blew it all away.

00:32:53.757 --> 00:32:55.017
Excuse me.

00:32:55.107 --> 00:32:57.153
Bankim didn't write
that in his book.

00:32:57.290 --> 00:32:58.595
Excuse...
- My lord!

00:33:02.058 --> 00:33:05.663
Lord, find a solution for me.
- What do you want?

00:33:06.048 --> 00:33:08.925
Take me to 1914 for
seven days, Baba.

00:33:09.015 --> 00:33:11.713
I will buy some cheap iron, Baba.
Please, Baba.

00:33:12.135 --> 00:33:15.733
Iron?
- Yes. Iron, sir. I mean, Lord.

00:33:16.155 --> 00:33:19.635
Cheap?
- Yes, Lord. From 1914.

00:33:19.823 --> 00:33:23.110
What do you do? - I am the
ledger keeper in a bell tea shop.

00:33:23.200 --> 00:33:26.452
Salary is just 233 rupees per month.
I can't manage my family with that.

00:33:27.068 --> 00:33:31.063
Can't manage your family?
- No. The iron, my Lord!

00:33:31.990 --> 00:33:36.515
Wealth does not come
so cheap, my man.

00:33:36.605 --> 00:33:39.048
Does not!

00:33:39.138 --> 00:33:41.303
Very strict meditation is required.

00:33:43.590 --> 00:33:45.260
From the Muladhar Chakra,

00:33:45.285 --> 00:33:47.675
you must control KulaKundali,
the source of power.

00:33:47.740 --> 00:33:50.162
Then you'll have to raise it
to the Sahasrar Lotus.

00:33:50.252 --> 00:33:53.143
This Sahasrar is the sun.

00:33:53.903 --> 00:33:56.255
That sun has

00:33:57.017 --> 00:33:59.328
to move backwards.

00:33:59.418 --> 00:34:02.428
You must make it move backwards.

00:34:02.717 --> 00:34:05.422
If you do not understand
the science behind the sun,

00:34:05.512 --> 00:34:09.125
you can't do it.

00:34:10.048 --> 00:34:13.570
And that is a matter
of huge expenditure.

00:34:13.950 --> 00:34:16.600
Then, sir. Sorry, Lord!

00:34:17.160 --> 00:34:20.385
Then is there no solution?

00:34:20.778 --> 00:34:22.827
Please, Lord. Find some

00:34:23.298 --> 00:34:25.913
solution for me.

00:34:26.302 --> 00:34:30.573
There is a solution!
- There is?

00:34:30.663 --> 00:34:34.578
Right at noon,
when the clock strikes 12,

00:34:34.923 --> 00:34:36.697
go to the terrace.

00:34:36.868 --> 00:34:40.217
On the terrace, look at the sun

00:34:40.898 --> 00:34:46.373
and then chant 108 times martanda!

00:34:46.528 --> 00:34:48.450
Martanda!

00:34:48.540 --> 00:34:52.315
But your eyes should not blink.

00:34:52.733 --> 00:34:55.868
Your tongue should not get dry.

00:34:56.038 --> 00:35:00.368
Only then. Tempora.

00:35:00.542 --> 00:35:03.620
Tempora.

00:35:03.800 --> 00:35:06.942
Boris.

00:35:07.155 --> 00:35:10.310
Nephic.

00:35:10.703 --> 00:35:13.803
Nitious.

00:35:14.357 --> 00:35:17.132
Nibhus.

00:35:17.345 --> 00:35:20.660
Nibhorus.

00:35:40.328 --> 00:35:41.442
Buchki.

00:35:42.092 --> 00:35:44.755
This man... He's...

00:35:45.032 --> 00:35:48.035
What?
- Great!

00:35:48.125 --> 00:35:50.898
But just postpone your
induction for a few days. Please.

00:35:51.163 --> 00:35:53.288
Thanks for your suggestion.

00:35:54.438 --> 00:35:57.292
Don't worry. I'm there.

00:35:57.382 --> 00:36:00.190
I'll fix everything.
- Come on now.

00:36:14.162 --> 00:36:17.405
Doesn't work. This Baba is a fraud.

00:36:17.623 --> 00:36:21.035
What? Has your faith disappeared?
- It's all rubbish!

00:36:21.602 --> 00:36:24.812
No trace of poison.
Only empty threats.

00:36:25.082 --> 00:36:27.862
If you have so much power,
then show a miracle or two.

00:36:27.952 --> 00:36:30.695
That he will not do.
All he does is talk

00:36:30.785 --> 00:36:32.522
about what he did in the Satta era.

00:36:32.705 --> 00:36:35.223
Who can do even that
these days, Nitai?

00:36:35.313 --> 00:36:37.957
Stare at the afternoon sun

00:36:38.047 --> 00:36:40.735
and chant a mantra.
You can't even bat your eyelashes.

00:36:40.895 --> 00:36:43.658
You try it and show me. Let me
see whether you blink or not.

00:36:43.957 --> 00:36:46.535
Is this some kind of a joke?

00:36:46.757 --> 00:36:48.383
That's where you went wrong.

00:36:48.473 --> 00:36:52.308
If he did it himself, he would
reduce the voltage of the sun.

00:36:52.683 --> 00:36:54.565
After all, I hear he moves
the moon and the sun.

00:36:55.400 --> 00:36:59.130
Nibaran, if you want to expose
that Baba, then I'm with you.

00:37:00.033 --> 00:37:01.557
Babaji's new get-up.

00:37:02.372 --> 00:37:04.490
Magician.
- How?

00:37:06.523 --> 00:37:08.910
I just saw Brahma.
- You saw Brahma?

00:37:09.645 --> 00:37:10.925
Sit.

00:37:15.465 --> 00:37:16.663
What do you mean you saw Brahma?

00:37:16.753 --> 00:37:19.415
I went over to their
place, Nibaran. - Why?

00:37:19.577 --> 00:37:22.383
I thought I'll meet Buchki
and fix up some thing.

00:37:22.850 --> 00:37:24.000
What?

00:37:24.495 --> 00:37:27.592
I knew I wouldn't be able
to meet her so I took her a letter.

00:37:27.923 --> 00:37:29.882
Another quotation?
- No!

00:37:29.972 --> 00:37:31.603
A poem.
- My, my!

00:37:32.163 --> 00:37:34.453
And what did you write?
- I wrote...

00:37:35.975 --> 00:37:39.248
Babaji's a fraud. But in my love...

00:37:40.102 --> 00:37:43.517
Can you go, Nitai?
- Just continue.

00:37:44.603 --> 00:37:47.012
I wrote, Babaji's a fraud.

00:37:47.102 --> 00:37:49.783
But my love for you
isn't fraudulent.

00:37:50.135 --> 00:37:53.235
If you opt for induction,
why then should I stay alive?

00:37:55.395 --> 00:37:57.123
That's it. Two lines.

00:37:58.960 --> 00:38:00.255
Couplet.

00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:05.285
Fine. So did you give her
the letter?

00:38:05.500 --> 00:38:09.260
Kind of. You see, Babaji
goes into a trance at seven,

00:38:09.350 --> 00:38:12.778
and then everybody leaves.
So I thought

00:38:12.922 --> 00:38:16.215
if I go there at eight,
I might get to meet her.

00:38:16.385 --> 00:38:18.350
But still to be on the safe side,

00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:20.388
I took the letter along with me.

00:38:20.575 --> 00:38:24.792
So, I reached there
at exactly eight.

00:38:30.993 --> 00:38:34.937
The house was silent except
for the striking of the clock.

00:38:35.213 --> 00:38:39.598
I was feeling a little nervous,
but still I entered inside.

00:38:42.195 --> 00:38:43.562
After climbing half the stairs,

00:38:43.587 --> 00:38:46.438
I felt as if there was
no one upstairs.

00:38:46.967 --> 00:38:50.178
Darn it!
After mustering up such courage,

00:38:50.268 --> 00:38:52.523
would I have to return
home hopeless?

00:38:52.850 --> 00:38:55.338
No. I must give it one last try.

00:38:55.590 --> 00:38:59.790
I thought I should check the
backyard and garden of the house.

00:39:00.983 --> 00:39:02.983
As I walked, I heard

00:39:03.142 --> 00:39:05.730
some strange sounds
emanating from there.

